  "title": "EEG data set for a architectural affordances task",
  "description": "This dataset comprises electroencephalography (EEG) recordings collected during an architectural affordances task. The study investigates neural correlates of spatial perception and environmental interaction using EEG acquisition. The dataset represents raw neurophysiological data suitable for cognitive neuroscience research on embodied cognition and environmental processing. This dataset is mirrored on NEMAR from OpenNeuro (ds004980).",
